description: Issue 16 marked a change in the style of cover art. The series would go on to use altered photographs rather than drawings for all future covers.
name: “L’ora della vendetta”

deck: Elisha Baekinsky goes solo and attempts to infiltrate the Reign network
description:
REIGN - A TENTACULAR TERRORIST ORGANISATION OF ANARCHISTS HOLDS PHILADELPHIA IN A GRIP OF FEAR.

A booby-trapped parcel has just gone off in a shopping mall, and two policemen have been killed. The cell fears the resurgence of an elusive terrorist organisation called Reign. Isaac is worried. For him, Reign reawaken long-buried memories...

A series led at a furious pace by the authors of Yiu PM. Action and suspense in the tradition of ‘The Bourne Ultimatum'.
name: Seconde chance

description: CHAOS NOW HAS A NAME... REIGN.The most dangerous man in the United States just revealed himself to the authorities: Grace Housemann, the head of the Reign terrorist network. Reign is ceaselessly expanding its domination on a planetary scale, the attacks keep adding up. Things point to Adam Nexe and Elisha Baekinski, who appear to play a major role in Reign. But behind the facade, what is Reign really planning? And how implicated is the government in the rise of this terrorist group?
name: Troisième escadre
Where Did We Come From? Who Are We? Where Are We Going?

description: This ended up being the last released issue of Infernal. A 26th issue was solicited but never published.
name: “Principessa Strip-tease”
